        <p>LEAD: Highlights of the major tax proposals under consideration by Congress. All are aimed at cutting the Federal deficit by $40 billion in fiscal year 1991, which began on Oct. 1 and by $500 billion over five years. Some variations in revenue projections reflect minor differences in the plans.</p>
